This README covers the installation of Intrelab, the
Intrepid/Matlab interface, along with the installation
of an interface to some Trilinos solvers, through ML.

1) Get a recent version of Trilinos.

2) Build Intrepid and solvers (ML, etc.) in shared library mode:

   - for release mode use options
      -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE:STRING=RELEASE \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_ALL_PACKAGES:BOOL=OFF \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_Amesos:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_AztecOO:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_Epetra:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_EpetraExt:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_Ifpack:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_ML:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_Teuchos:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_Intrepid:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_ALL_OPTIONAL_PACKAGES:BOOL=OFF \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_TESTS:BOOL=OFF \
      -D BUILD_SHARED_LIBS:BOOL=ON \
      -D TPL_ENABLE_BinUtils=OFF \
      -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX:PATH=/YOUR_INSTALL_PATH_HERE \

   - for debug mode use options
      -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE:STRING=DEBUG \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_ALL_PACKAGES:BOOL=OFF \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_Amesos:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_AztecOO:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_Epetra:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_EpetraExt:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_Ifpack:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_ML:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_Teuchos:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_Intrepid:BOOL=ON \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_ALL_OPTIONAL_PACKAGES:BOOL=OFF \
      -D Trilinos_ENABLE_TESTS:BOOL=OFF \
      -D BUILD_SHARED_LIBS:BOOL=ON \
      -D TPL_ENABLE_BinUtils=OFF \
      -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX:PATH=/YOUR_INSTALL_PATH_HERE \

   Also see Trilinos compile scripts contained in
     scripts/cmake.intrepid+ML.shared.release
   and
     scripts/cmake.intrepid+ML.shared.debug

3) Modify the two makefiles, Makefile (for fast optimized interface)
   and Makefile.debug (if debugging is needed).

4) Run

   make -j12

5) Modify matlab startup scripts run_matlab_release.sh and run_matlab_debug.sh.
   Note that the modifications will depend on your platform, your version
   of Matlab, etc.  Some trial and error may be needed.  The main goal is to
   make Matlab aware of the library paths and the versions of BLAS and LAPACK
   used by Trilinos.  If Matlab's default BLAS and LAPACK (MKL) are used,
   there could be problems.

6) Start matlab using run_matlab_release.sh (or run_matlab_debug.sh, if
   debugging is needed).

7) To test the install of Intrelab discretizations, run the matlab script
   m2i_test and check output.

8) For the testing of ML solver capabilities, run m2ml_test and
   check output.

9) Obtain and play with the poisson_fem example.
